author: The Columbus Dispatch
title: Ohio State vs. Rutgers | Three points | Buckeye Xtra Sports
text:
>> Got a question about Ohio State football? Ask the experts! 
Star of the week Quarterback J.T. Barrett made his first start of the season and amassed more than 300 yards of total offense, including throwing for three touchdowns and running for two. He is now responsible for 59 TDs over two seasons.
>> Get the most out of your Ohio State experience, follow @BuckeyeXtra on Twitter 
Turning point Barrett’s 2-yard touchdown run at 3:02 of the second quarter put Ohio State ahead 21-0. The Buckeyes were cold at the start, but by the middle of the second quarter, Barrett had warmed the tires. From 6:48 of the second to 4:34 of the third, they scored five touchdowns.
>> Click for details on how to win tickets and trips to OSU games from Dispatch Reader Rewards 
Repercussions It was Ohio State’s 28th straight Big Ten regular-season win, one short of the all-time national conference record of 29 by Florida State in the early 1990s. And it was OSU’s 21st straight victory, longest active streak in the country.
